<h2 class="text-center">This man is a real inspiration wether you are fan of him or not, although i am his fan, but i can pretty much say he is an example of a great, hard-working man.
</h2>


<h3>Born Cristiano Ronaldo dos Santos Aveiro on February 5, 1985, in Funchal, Madeira, Portugal, a small island off the western coast of the country, Ronaldo is the youngest of four children born to Maria Dolores dos Santos and Jose Dinis Aveiro. He was named after Ronald Reagan, one of his father's favorite actors.
</h3>

<h4><em>Here are some of the things which makes him a great guy:</em></h4>
<ul>
  <li>He has no talent, still he became one the best players of the world.</li>
  <li>Yes, he has great height, but still he worked than any other person to reach this level.</li>
  <li>He comes to the training before anyone, and leaves the last.</li>
  <li>What's even greater than all that, he is a great human! how so? here:
    <ol>
      <li>In 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami showed an eight-year-old boy survivor named Martunis wearing a number 7 Portuguese football shirt who was stranded for 19 days after his family was killed.Following this, Ronaldo visited Aceh, Indonesia,
        to raise funds for rehabilitation and reconstruction.</li>
      <li>Ronaldo Donated £100,000 to the hospital that saved his mother's life in Madeira following her battle with cancer</li>
      <li> In November 2012, Ronaldo sold the golden boot he had won in 2011 for €1.5 million and gave the money to fund schools for children in Gaza.</li>
      <li>Least, he was named the world's most charitable sportsperson in 2015, and many more Philanthropies.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>Not to mention the tons of individuals awards he has.</li>
</ul>

